## What changed since Update 2 (14 July)

**The single remaining code gap is closed.** Update 2 flagged that the two new
cron workers (`outbox-sweep`, `raw-email-purge`) existed in the repo but were not
deployed by any CI workflow. They are now wired into `deploy-demo.yml` as two new
jobs (`deploy-outbox-sweep`, `deploy-raw-email-purge`), mirroring `deploy-keepalive`.

- Each job ships **code + vars only**. Their `CRON_SECRET` (and `CF_ACCESS_*` if the
  target is behind Access) remain `wrangler secret put` secrets the founder sets once.
- **Semantics to know:** both workers' `TARGET_URL` defaults to **PROD**
  (`usedcarsnz.co.nz/api/cron/*`), but the only CI in the repo is `deploy-demo.yml`
  (triggered by pushes to the `demo` branch). So they deploy on demo-branch pushes.
  Re-deploys are idempotent; this is the pragmatic wiring given prod has no CI of its
  own. If a dedicated prod-cron workflow is ever wanted, split them out then.

**Also confirmed merged to `develop`:** `feature/prompt7-closeout` (PR #30) and the
listing-less draft fix (PR #31). The "verification gate" from Update 2 is therefore
**moot** — that branch is already on `develop`. Nothing to merge.

Everything else Update 2 verified as done (latency-check, DEMO_RUNBOOK, `/privacy`,
image compression, page ISR, noindex, roadmap) remains done.

